</select>";s:6:"parent";s:2:"62";s:5:"count";s:2:"11";}i:12;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"38";s:4:"name";s:5:"Films";s:4:"slug";s:5:"films";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"38";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:6:"parent";s:1:"1";s:5:"count";s:2:"24";}i:13;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"67";s:4:"name";s:8:"Freeware";s:4:"slug";s:8:"freeware";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"67";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:267:"The goodies, free stuff to play with and test, map match mix manipulate all without worrying how much you have in you wallet. Note: Even if it's on our amazing WebMag, you may want to check for any viruses or other malicious bugs that may cause harm to your computer.";s:6:"parent";s:2:"62";s:5:"count";s:2:"21";}i:15;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"62";s:4:"name";s:8:"Learning";s:4:"slug";s:8:"learning";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"62";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:2255:"With technologies constantly evolving even the pros are learning new things all the time, isn't this what makes the VJ scene interesting and challenging at the same time. In this category you'll find a diversity of information in posts: to get up and started, everything to feed your brains thirst, or to perfect your skills and explore more technics or methods, and become knowledgeable on those complex tools that we use to make audio visual art and installations. On each page you'll notice drop down bars displayed  just over the posts to quickly find what you are looking for without browsing every page. You can explore <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/books/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Books</span></a> by subject or tool of choice and even select by author, in <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/community/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Community</span></a> you can read articles about organizations playing a role in the VJ scene and even in the industry, make sure to network and support to really get out there. Not sure where to start? No fears we've all been there, in <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/education/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Education</span></a> there is degrees you might want to consider or/and if that's not an option there are courses available for anyone to register. <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/freeware/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Freeware,</span></a> free goodies! yup that's right, all of them and that's not all, in <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/open-source-code/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Open Source</span></a> with it's full flexibility, is what you coding creatives and hacking lunatics are looking for, updates on the the latest geeky stuff out there, well at least we'll make sure it's up to date for you. Budget sometimes limits our options, well guess what? developers of those great live software you use, they made lot's of <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/learning/tutorials/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Tutorials</span></a> just for you so you can get a hold of it, and if that's not enough there are <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/tag/workshops/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Workshops</span></a> you might want to follow in a city near you.
";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:17;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"34";s:4:"name";s:5:"Music";s:4:"slug";s:5:"music";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"34";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:276:"Visuals aren't complimentary, they make a lasting impression because we are visual creatures and that is why we will present music performances and music videos that speak to our ears and eyes. In some cases it may just be an installation for a concert or tools that are used.";s:6:"parent";s:1:"1";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:18;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:1:"1";s:4:"name";s:4:"News";s:4:"slug";s:4:"news";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:1:"1";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:1852:"Follow the latest and the coolest news on the VJ scene with <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/interviews/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Interviews</span></a> of talented artists and performers from around the world, audio visual or <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/music/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Music</span></a> <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/performances/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Performances</span></a> during <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/festivals/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Festivals</span></a> or smaller <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/events/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Events</span></a> and <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/tag/workshops/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Workshops</span></a> near you, no matter where you are on your computer or smart phone. Check out awesome video <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/animated/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Animations</span></a> and <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/animated/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Animated</span></a> images using different technics and <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/product-release/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Products</span></a> we will point out and explain to you, or creative <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/av-space/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">AV Spaces</span></a> made by designers and media art companies that may be part of <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/films/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Films</span></a> sets, of a <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/news/music/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Music</span></a> concert installation and even integrated into the interior architecture. All this nicely presented on our site just for you, if you want to let us know of the latest stuff send it on our <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/submit/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Submit</span></a> page.";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"2";}i:19;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:3:"244";s:4:"name";s:11:"Open Source";s:4:"slug";s:16:"open-source-code";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:3:"268";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:441:"Source codes, Processing projects, Cinder stuff, openFrameworks to work it, Java logics and tricks, C++ extras, JavaScript in words, Hacks made clear, Glitch twicks, linux pinguines, ....you name it, we post it. Well would be cool if you could post us too on the <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/submit/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Submit</span></a> page, not that we are lazy but hey.. you may have some cool stuff we don't know about. ;0)";s:6:"parent";s:2:"62";s:5:"count";s:1:"1";}i:21;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"35";s:4:"name";s:15:"Product Release";s:4:"slug";s:15:"product-release";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"35";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:129:"The newest products, creative gadgets, cool applications, futuristic technology and even stuff you can wear to look like a robot.";s:6:"parent";s:1:"1";s:5:"count";s:1:"6";}i:23;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"25";s:4:"name";s:7:"Reviews";s:4:"slug";s:7:"reviews";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"25";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:1721:"First things first, you will need to buy tools to start creating content,to  prepare your set or make an installation for your next event and maybe even <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/projection/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Project</span></a> your visuals on a wall. Here we will review <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/applications/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Applications</span></a> you may want to use on your mobile devices or computer, or analog instruments to create <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/video/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Video</span></a> or <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/audio-reviews/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Audio</span></a>, but you may want to start getting serious and perform/produce more intuitively with <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/controllers/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Controllers</span></a> we have our hands on and will show you here. Once you are done with this part you may be looking for a <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/projection/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Projector</span></a> as we mentioned earlier, or different <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/electronics/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Electronics</span></a> to create an interactive surface or integrated system for your art concept with digital <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/reviews/lighting/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Lighting</span></a> to illuminate the hole thing. Once you made your choice out of all the different products we reviewed and presented, you will be all set and we hope to see your work soon in our inbox submitted through the <a href="http://www.vjsmag.com/submit/"><span style="color: #3366ff;">Submit</span></a> page.";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}i:24;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:2:"66";s:4:"name";s:9:"Tutorials";s:4:"slug";s:9:"tutorials";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:2:"66";s:8:"taxonomy";s:8:"category";s:11:"description";s:3208:"This page contains t